gentlemen. Whether it be that Mercurie is Lord of their birth,
or some other peeuish planet predominant in the calculation of
their natiuitie, I know not: but this I am sure, that theyr rype
wittes are so soone ouershadowed with vice, and their senses so
blinded with self loue, that they make their choyce so farre without
skill, as they proue them selues but euill chapmen: for if she
be faire, they thinke her faithfull: if her bodye be endued with
bewtie, they iudge she cannot but be vertuous. They are so bli
