webbe wherein to be tangled. The flye, as she is reuiued
by the heate of the Sunne, so is she consumed by the flame of
the fire: as the Lyon cooleth his stomacke with eating the Seamouse,
so is it inflamed with eating the litle Ermelyne. But
although in this respect I cannot greatly eyther accuse nature
or fortune, yet the destinies I thinke haue framed your bewtie
such a furious enemy to my carefull minde, as it hath made such
a breach in my heart, that the strongest rampyre and surest defence
