                bed, yet
she her self knew scarsly the disease: but Pharicles missing her,
went farder, and sound Madam Castilla sitting solytary in her
Muses, whom after he had saluted and demaunded how mistres
Mamillia did: Mary quoth Madam Castilla, your often repair
vnto her, as farre as we can coniecture, hath driuen her into a
plurisie, or vs into som ielousie: but whether it did she is sicke.
            
               Pharicles, feeling his gald conscience prick
                  •
                sayd, that although
it pleased her to iest by cōtraries, yet his return was as
speedy, as might be: for his busines was so necessary, that the
