            You speak wel, quoth Madam Castilla: therefore follow me,
that you may plead your owne cause for I will be no Aduocat:
and with that she caried him into Mamillias chamber, where
she lay, half sleeping, half waking, whom Madam Castilla called
out of her traunce with this parle.
            MIstres Mamillia, quoth she, you know whē time was, we
tearmed this Gentleman a gostly father: therfore I thoght
good in this your sickenes, that he should receiue your cōfession,

as one most meete for the purpose I thank you for your paines,
quoth Mamillia: for indeede I haue a great block in my conscience,
which I meane to reueale vnto him, &amp; that is of my folly,
in louing so lightly, and fixing my fancy, where I doubt is no
